Rating: 4
This recipe is fantastic and is on the roster to be a "go to". It's delicious as is, or a great base for modification: Throwing in some spinach or swapping out the shrimp for chicken, are both great options. Also, frozen peeled shrimp from Trader Joes works great in this. **As for the recipe itself** the only major modification I'd do has been mentioned before: anticipate longer cooking time for the sauce by pulling out the shrimp while the sauce is made. Admittedly, I haven't gotten the sauce consistency perfect quite yet, but that should only take one more try. The first time I made it, it was incredibly runny; the second time a tad too thick. So, I recommend holding on to some of the pasta water so you've got something to work with if you over-cook it. Two other points, with regard to the sauce consistency: Adding the lemon juice thickens it a bit, so don't skimp. Letting it sit for a couple minutes does as well. Beyond that, my only modifications are to give each plate an extra squirt of lemon and a bit of chopped fresh parsley before serving. Store leftover pasta and sauce together; the pasta will sop up the sauce, and everything will taste twice as good the next day.

